@node "installation" "MoneyManager: Installation"
@smartwrap
To install MoneyManager to your harddisk just use the supplied Installer
script.
@endnode

@node "newproject" "MoneyManager: New Project"
@smartwrap
The first thing you have to do is to choose the 'New' menu item.

Afterwards you should select the 'Accounts' button which is located in the
'Edit' box in the main window.

Now a new window with 5 name gadgets and 5 value gadgets will pop up.

The name gadgets are in the left side of the window and the value gadgets
are in the right side of the window.

The name gadgets are supposed to contain the names of your accounts.

The value gadgets are supposed to contain the start values of your accounts.

When you have finished your editing then press the 'Ok' button in the
bottom of the window.

If you have made a mistake somewhere you can always go back and change the
names and startvalues of your accounts.
@endnode

@node "dateformat" "MoneyManager: Dateformat"
@smartwrap
The dateformat used by MoneyManager is: dd/mm/yyyy meaning


  dd: This is the day

  mm: This is the month

yyyy: This is the year (Four digits are used to avoid any Y2K problems :-) )


@{b}Examples:@{ub}


@{b}1. May 1999:@{ub} 01/05/1999 (Allways remember the trailing zeros else you will get a requester saying wrong dateformat!)


@{b}31. December 1999:@{ub} 31/12/1999

@endnode

@node "butopen" "MoneyManager: Open"
@smartwrap
Opens a filerequester where you can select a MoneyManager project to load.
@endnode

@node "butsave" "MoneyManager: Save"
@smartwrap
Opens a filerequester where you can select a MoneyManager project to save.
@endnode

@node "butinfo" "MoneyManager: Information"
@smartwrap
Gives you some information about the current project.
@endnode

@node "butnewtrans" "MoneyManager: New Transaction"
@smartwrap
Opens a window where you can choose what account you want to affect and what
type of transaction you want.

In addition you can give the transaction a comment.

When you have finished the transaction editing then just press the 'Ok' button.

@{"[PICTURE]" link "NewTransaction.IFF/Main" 0}


@endnode

@node "butnewtransf" "MoneyManager: New Transfer"
If you want to transfer some money from one account to another then choose the
'New transfer' button and you will get a window where you can define the value
of the transfer and the from and to accounts.
@endnode

@node "butaccounts" "MoneyManager: Accounts"
The 'Account' button lists the incomes and expenses in one account. The
account you want to list is selected with the cycle button in the bottom of
the window.
@endnode

@node "buttags" "MoneyManager: Tags"
@endnode

@node "butaccount" "MoneyManager: Account"
List the total transaction for one account. The account is selected with the
cyclegadget in the bottom of the window.
@endnode

@node "butincomes" "MoneyManager: Incomes"
The 'Incomes' button lists all the incomes. The delete button in the bottom of
the window deletes the currently selected income. The edit button in the
bottom of the window is used to edit the currently selected item. The edit
window is exactly the same as the 'New transaction' window. The only
difference is that you will not be able to change the type of transaction.
@endnode

@node "butexpenses" "MoneyManager: Expenses"
The 'Expenses' button lists all the exepenses. The delete button in the bottom
of the window deletes the currently selected expense. The edit button in the
bottom of the window is used to edit the currently selected item. The edit
window is exactly the same as the 'New transaction' window. The only
difference is that you will not be able to change the type of transaction.
@endnode

@node "butbalance" "MoneyManager: Balance"
The 'Balance' button lists the balance of one or all the accounts. The list to
be shown is selected with the cycle gadget in the bottom of the window.
@endnode

