@node "bugs" "MoneyManager: Bugs"
@smartwrap
MoneyManager is in no way a perfect program and I'm quite sure that there's a
whole lot of bugs for you to discover. Though there should be no bugs doing
bad things to your hardware/software.


The graph function is still in a very experimental state. This means that the
graph output could be corrupted if you use another System Default font than
the Topaz size 8/XEN size 9 font or a similar font. This will be corrected in
future versions of MoneyManager. In addition some of the graph drawing rotines
seems a bit broken. This causes that the highest point on the graph not always
follows the axes. (Though the graph is still drawn as it should it just
doesn't use the whole window)


The encryption routine is very simple and it cannot be used to keep real
hardcore hackers out of your files but your mother/brother/father/girlfriend
or whoever who has access to your computer will probably not be able to break
the encryption. If you load an encrypted file by doubleclicking it's icon you
will get a warning requester saying 'Please reload file!'. If you don't do
this your comments will be nothing but garbage. Another bug in the encryption
is that even though you don't now the password you are still able to load the
file and see the values of all transactions and accounts. This will be
corrected as soon as possible.


This AmigaGuide document is a bug too. It is in no way finished and maybe it
will never be. Mainly because I hate writing docs. I prefer to spend my time
developing the program. (If this is problem for anybody then please mail me
and if enough requests this I will probably do something about it in the
future.)


Please email me about any bugs you find see @{"Address" link "address" 0}.

@endnode

@node "history" "MoneyManager: History"
@smartwrap
@{b}08/01/1999 1.0@{ub}

First public version (To be considered as a public beta!)

@{b}26/06/1999 1.1 Beta 1@{ub}

* Sorting is now a lot faster when adding transactions in date order.

* Added pie chart graphing. (But you can't change the parameters. It's only here to show you that I was working on it.)

* Improved the "Show Tags" option.

* The problem with tags not being loaded on startup now fixed (very stupid bug).

* Improved the GUI somewhat.

* Graphing is disabled for the moment (It sucks. But you can see the changed GUI).

* Now it's possible to show intervals of tags (from one date to another).

* Deletion of tags now works as it should.

* It's now possible to change the names and abreviations of tags!

* Added possibility to save data as a GNUPlot compatible datafile.

* Added a datecheck routine to prevent wrong dateformats. (Not used everywhere yet.)

* Bubble help added. (Only when the pointer is over the date field in the 'New Transaction' window.)

@endnode

